      },
      "date": "2014-10-28 17:19:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI think it would be safer to disallow GID=0 for grouplocks.\n\nThe reason is that this could incorrectly be used by code in either the kernel or userspace if the GID field is uninitialized, and allow two separate applications or instances of applications to access a file concurrently when they shouldn't.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bb0e3bdd94b497c90033fb14e045090cde2b427e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-28 17:46:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks, Andreas.  Good point.  Oleg made a similar one in LU-5817.  I'll make a patch to return -EINVAL with gid 0 instead.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
